Not quite — the `vi.stubGlobal` is wrapping the test on line 62, which breaks the structure. It needs to go **inside** the test function, before the `return`. Look at how the search test does it:

```js
test("some test name", () => {
    vi.stubGlobal("fetch", () =>        // <-- first: mock fetch
      Promise.resolve({
        ok: true,
        json: () => Promise.resolve(...),
      }),
    );
    return request(app)                  // <-- then: make the request
      .post(...)
});
```

So for your "saves the favorite" test, the structure should be:

```
test("saves the favorite and returns 201 with the created row", () => {
    vi.stubGlobal("fetch", () =>
      Promise.resolve({
        ok: true,
        json: () => Promise.resolve({ data: { title: "Naruto" } }),
      }),
    );
    return request(app)
      .post("/api/favorites")
      ...
});
```

The `vi.stubGlobal` is a **statement inside the test**, not wrapping it. Same thing for the delete test on line 88.

Try again!

