OK. Your test on line 62 currently looks like this (roughly):

```
test("saves the favorite and returns 201 with the created row", () => {
    vi.stubGlobal("fetch",()=>{ return request(app)
    ...
```

Let's rebuild it. There are exactly **three parts** inside the test function:

### Part 1 — The mock (a complete statement)

This tells JavaScript: "whenever anyone calls `fetch()`, return this fake response instead."

```
vi.stubGlobal("fetch", () =>
  Promise.resolve({
    ok: true,
    json: () => Promise.resolve({ data: { title: "Naruto" } }),
  }),
);
```

That's one statement, ending with `;`. It has nothing to do with `request(app)`.

### Part 2 — The test request (a separate statement)

```
return request(app)
  .post("/api/favorites")
  ...the rest of your test stays the same
```

### Part 3 — Close the test

```
});
```

So the full structure is:

```
test("saves the favorite...", () => {
    // Part 1: mock
    vi.stubGlobal(...);

    // Part 2: test
    return request(app).post(...).expect(...);
});
```

Write Part 1 first, put a `;` at the end, then write Part 2 starting with `return request(app)`. Keep the rest of the test body the same as before.

Do the same for the delete test (line 88) — add the same `vi.stubGlobal` before the `return request(app)`.

Give it a try!

